title: H2O Sunday Service
description: The purpose of our Sunday Service is to gather together to worship God as a family. We believe that it is not just a meeting, but an opportunity to hear from God through His Word and through others. No matter where you are in your faith journey, you are welcome to join us as you are every Sunday. You can expect: Authentic worship music so that we may praise Him together Solid Biblical teaching that applies to your life Real stories about what God is doing in people’s lives Conversation and fellowship before and after each gathering Our Sunday Services are at 10:30am on campus every week!
descriptionHtml:
The purpose of our Sunday Service is to gather together to worship God as a family. We believe that it is not just a meeting, but an opportunity to hear from God through His Word and through others. No matter where you are in your faith journey, you are welcome to join us as you are every Sunday.

You can expect:

  • Authentic worship music so that we may praise Him together
  • Solid Biblical teaching that applies to your life
  • Real stories about what God is doing in people’s lives
  • Conversation and fellowship before and after each gathering

Our Sunday Services are at 10:30am on campus every week!

title: Making Friends at UB: From Hellos to Hangouts
title_lowercase: making friends at ub: from hellos to hangouts
description: Making friends at a large school, like UB, can feel overwhelming—where do you even start? There's no shame in not knowing. This workshop is all about turning those awkward hellos into real hangouts. We’ll talk through the challenges of meeting new people in such a large community and give you simple, practical strategies to connect with your peers. From starting conversations to growing casual acquaintances into genuine friendships, you’ll leave with actionable steps. Whether you’re outgoing, introverted, or somewhere in between, this session will help you feel more confident about building your social circle at UB.

title: Group Quiet Study: Mondays
description: Join Accessibility Resources in group quiet study sessions every week on Monday. These sessions will utilize the Pomodoro Technique, a time management strategy that involves splitting work tasks into 25-minute intervals, known as pomodoros, with breaks scheduled in between each interval. This technique is a productive strategy to complete tasks that you might otherwise find challenging. Light snacks, coloring sheets, and word puzzles are available during breaks. Join virtually or in person and work with other students, helping you focus on your tasks. Monday's session will be hybrid.
